form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Petition by United States Citizen for Issuance of Immigrant Visa, Form I-133

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/11/2023 Form I-133 Form approved. UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUST Budget Bureau No. 43-R029.7. IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION SERVI File No. (Rev. 7-2-53) PETITION BY UNITED STATES CITIZEN FOR ISSUANCE OF IMMIGRANT VISA IMPORTANT.-Do not use this form unless you are a United States citizen and are petitioning for your wife, husband, child (regardless of age), parent, brother, or sister. See instruction No. 4 for cases in which petitions cannot be approved. This form must be typewritten or printed legibly with pen and ink, and submitted in duplicate, unless you are petitioning for more than one beneficiary (see instruction No. 3), in which case a copy for each Consulate at which applications for visas will be made must be submitted. If you are residing in the United States, send the completed petition, in duplicate, to the office of the Immigration and Naturalization Service located nearest to your place of residence. If you are residing outside the United States, mail the petition to the Commissioner of Immigration and Naturalization, Washington 25, D. C., United States of America. You must answer ALL of the numbered questions and all other questions which may be applicable. Attach the required remittance in the sum of $10. (See instruction on last page.)
